{
    "type": "Style",
    "definition": "A style is a definition of color and opacity in case of a polygon body, and color, opacity and line thickness in case of polygon borders.",
    "paragraphs": [
        {
            "style": "Block",
            "text": "Content"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "A style applied to a polygon body or a polygon border node acts as the default style. Styles including colors, opacity, line width, and more, are defined in the node's configuration."
        },
        {
            "style": "Note",
            "text": "See the configuration for further details."
        },
        {
            "style": "Title",
            "text": "Adding a Style"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "To add a style, select Add Style on a polygon border or polygon body node menu."
        },
        {
            "style": "Title",
            "text": "Configuring Style"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "Select Configure Style on the menu to access the configuration."
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "A typical definition for a polygon body style looks like this:"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "{"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "    \"default\": {"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"opacity\": 0.2,"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"paletteColor\": \"UI_COLOR.DARK_TURQUOISE\""
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "    },"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "    \"atMousePosition\": {"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"opacity\": 0.3,"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"paletteColor\": \"UI_COLOR.DARK_TURQUOISE\""
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "    }"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "}"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "A typical definition for a polygon border style has a couple more properties:"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "{"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "    \"default\": {"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"opacity\": 0.2,"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"lineWidth\": 1,"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"lineDash\": [0,0],"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"paletteColor\": \"UI_COLOR.DARK_TURQUOISE\""
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "    },"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "    \"atMousePosition\": {"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"opacity\": 0.3,"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"lineWidth\": 2,"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"lineDash\": [0,0],"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "        \"paletteColor\": \"UI_COLOR.RUSTED_RED\""
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "    }"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "}"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "The first section of the definition refers, as explicitly stated, to the default state of the style."
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "The second section refers to the style assigned to the column or period on which the mouse pointer is located. This is very useful for highlighting the specific zone of interest as the user browses the charts."
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "opacity is probably self-explanatory: it may range from 0 for a fully transparent object to 1 for a solid object."
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| Variable Value | RGB Value | Color Sample |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| :--- | :---: | :------------------- |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| DARK | 48, 48, 54 | RGB(48, 48, 54) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| LIGHT | 234, 226, 222 | RGB(234, 226, 222); border: 1px black |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| GREY | 150, 150, 150 | RGB(150, 150, 150) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| LIGHT_GREY | 247, 247, 247 | RGB(247, 247, 247) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| WHITE | 255, 255, 255 | RGB(255, 255, 255) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| BLACK | 0, 0, 0 | RGB(0, 0, 0) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| GOLDEN_ORANGE | 240, 162, 2 | RGB(240, 162, 2) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| RUSTED_RED | 204, 88, 53 | RGB(204, 88, 53) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| GREEN | 188, 214, 67 | RGB(188, 214, 67) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| RED | 223, 70, 60 | RGB(223, 70, 60) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| PATINATED_TURQUOISE | 27, 153, 139 | RGB(27, 153, 139) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| TITANIUM_YELLOW | 244, 228, 9 | RGB(244, 228, 9) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| MANGANESE_PURPLE | 91,80, 122 | RGB(91,80, 122) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| TURQUOISE | 74, 207, 217 | RGB(74, 207, 217) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "Text",
            "text": "| DARK_TURQUOISE | 2, 149, 170 | RGB(2, 149, 170) |"
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "lineWidth is the width of the border line, which should be greater than 0."
        },
        {
            "style": "List",
            "text": "lineDash is used to turn the border into a dashed-line; the first value corresponds to the length of the dash while the second value defines the length of the space."
        }
    ]
}